32/* Define a set of ISAs which are available when a given ISA is
33 enabled. MMX and SSE ISAs are handled separately. */
34
35#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX
36#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_SET \
37 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW | OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_SET)
38#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_A_SET \
39 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_A | OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_SET)
40
41#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE
42#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE2_SET \
43 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE2 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_SET)

51 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_2 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_1_SET)
52#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_SET \
53 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX | OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_2_SET \
54 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_XSAVE_SET)
55#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_FMA_SET \
56 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_FMA | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_SET)
57#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_SET \

60#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_XSAVE_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_XSAVE

62 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_XSAVEOPT | OPTION_MASK_ISA_XSAVE)
63#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_SET \
64 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_SET)
65#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512CD_SET \

70 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512ER | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_SET)

76 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VL | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_SET)
77#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512IFMA_SET \
78 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512IFMA | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_SET)
79#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VBMI_SET \
80 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VBMI | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512BW_SET)
81#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124FMAPS_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124FMAPS
82#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124VNNIW_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124VNNIW
83#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VPOPCNTDQ_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VPOPCNTDQ
84#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_RTM_SET OPTION_MASK_ISA_RTM

164#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_UNSET \
165 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX | OPTION_MASK_ISA_FMA_UNSET \
166 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_FMA4_UNSET | OPTION_MASK_ISA_F16C_UNSET \
167 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_UNSET | OPTION_MASK_ISA_XSAVE_UNSET)

187#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512IFMA_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512IFMA
188#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VBMI_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VBMI
189#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124FMAPS_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124FMAPS
190#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124VNNIW_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124VNNIW
191#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VPOPCNTDQ_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VPOPCNTDQ
192#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_RTM_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_RTM
193#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_PRFCHW_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_PRFCHW
194#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_RDSEED_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_RDSEED
195#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_ADX_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_ADX
196#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_PREFETCHWT1_UNSET OPTION_MASK_ISA_PREFETCHWT1

237#define OPTION_MASK_ISA_GENERAL_REGS_ONLY_UNSET \
238 (OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_UNSET \
239 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_UNSET \
240 | OPTION_MASK_ISA_MPX)

242/* Implement TARGET_HANDLE_OPTION. */
243
244bool
245ix86_handle_option (struct gcc_options *opts,
246 struct gcc_options *opts_set ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
247 const struct cl_decoded_option *decoded,
248 location_t loc)
249{
250 size_t code = decoded->opt_index;
251 int value = decoded->value;
252
253 switch (code)
254 {
255 case OPT_mgeneral_regs_only:
256 if (value)
257 {
258 /* Disable MPX, MMX, SSE and x87 instructions if only
259 general registers are allowed. */
260 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags
261 &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_GENERAL_REGS_ONLY_UNSET;
262 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit
263 |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_GENERAL_REGS_ONLY_UNSET;
264
265 opts->x_target_flags &= ~MASK_80387;
266 }
267 else
268 gcc_unreachable ();
269 return true;
270
271 case OPT_mmmx:
272 if (value)
273 {
274 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_SET;
275 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_SET;
276 }
277 else
278 {
279 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_UNSET;
280 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_MMX_UNSET;
281 }
282 return true;
283
284 case OPT_m3dnow:
285 if (value)
286 {
287 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_SET;
288 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_SET;
289 }
290 else
291 {
292 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_UNSET;
293 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_UNSET;
294 }
295 return true;
296
297 case OPT_m3dnowa:
298 if (value)
299 {
300 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_A_SET;
301 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_A_SET;
302 }
303 else
304 {
305 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_A_UNSET;
306 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_3DNOW_A_UNSET;
307 }
308 return true;
309
310 case OPT_msse:
311 if (value)
312 {
313 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_SET;
314 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_SET;
315 }
316 else
317 {
318 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_UNSET;
319 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE_UNSET;
320 }
321 return true;
322
323 case OPT_msse2:
324 if (value)
325 {
326 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE2_SET;
327 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE2_SET;
328 }
329 else
330 {
331 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE2_UNSET;
332 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE2_UNSET;
333 }
334 return true;
335
336 case OPT_msse3:
337 if (value)
338 {
339 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE3_SET;
340 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE3_SET;
341 }
342 else
343 {
344 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE3_UNSET;
345 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE3_UNSET;
346 }
347 return true;
348
349 case OPT_mssse3:
350 if (value)
351 {
352 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSSE3_SET;
353 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSSE3_SET;
354 }
355 else
356 {
357 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSSE3_UNSET;
358 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSSE3_UNSET;
359 }
360 return true;
361
362 case OPT_msse4_1:
363 if (value)
364 {
365 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_1_SET;
366 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_1_SET;
367 }
368 else
369 {
370 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_1_UNSET;
371 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_1_UNSET;
372 }
373 return true;
374
375 case OPT_msse4_2:
376 if (value)
377 {
378 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_2_SET;
379 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_2_SET;
380 }
381 else
382 {
383 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_2_UNSET;
384 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_SSE4_2_UNSET;
385 }
386 return true;
387
388 case OPT_mavx:
389 if (value)
390 {
391 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_SET;
392 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_SET;
393 }
394 else
395 {
396 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_UNSET;
397 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX_UNSET;
398 }
399 return true;
400
401 case OPT_mavx2:
402 if (value)
403 {
404 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_SET;
405 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_SET;
406 }
407 else
408 {
409 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_UNSET;
410 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX2_UNSET;
411 }
412 return true;
413
414 case OPT_mavx512f:
415 if (value)
416 {
417 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_SET;
418 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_SET;
419 }
420 else
421 {
422 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_UNSET;
423 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512F_UNSET;
424
425 /* Turn off additional isa flags. */
426 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags2 &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124FMAPS_UNSET;
427 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags2_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124FMAPS_UNSET;
428 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags2 &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124VNNIW_UNSET;
429 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags2_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX5124VNNIW_UNSET;
430 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags2 &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VPOPCNTDQ_UNSET;
431 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags2_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512VPOPCNTDQ_UNSET;
432 }
433 return true;
434
435 case OPT_mavx512cd:
436 if (value)
437 {
438 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512CD_SET;
439 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512CD_SET;
440 }
441 else
442 {
443 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512CD_UNSET;
444 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512CD_UNSET;
445 }
446 return true;
447
448 case OPT_mavx512pf:
449 if (value)
450 {
451 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512PF_SET;
452 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512PF_SET;
453 }
454 else
455 {
456 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags &= ~OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512PF_UNSET;
457 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512PF_UNSET;
458 }
459 return true;
460
461 case OPT_mavx512er:
462 if (value)
463 {
464 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512ER_SET;
465 opts->x_ix86_isa_flags_explicit |= OPTION_MASK_ISA_AVX512ER_SET;
466 }

1088
1089 /* Comes from final.c -- no real reason to change it. */
1090#define MAX_CODE_ALIGN 16
1091
1092 case OPT_malign_loops_:
1093 warning_at (loc, 0, "-malign-loops is obsolete, use -falign-loops");
1094 if (value > MAX_CODE_ALIGN)
1095 error_at (loc, "-malign-loops=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1096 value, MAX_CODE_ALIGN);
1097 else
1098 opts->x_align_loops = 1 << value;
1099 return true;
1100
1101 case OPT_malign_jumps_:
1102 warning_at (loc, 0, "-malign-jumps is obsolete, use -falign-jumps");
1103 if (value > MAX_CODE_ALIGN)
1104 error_at (loc, "-malign-jumps=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1105 value, MAX_CODE_ALIGN);
1106 else
1107 opts->x_align_jumps = 1 << value;
1108 return true;
1109
1110 case OPT_malign_functions_:
1111 warning_at (loc, 0,
1112 "-malign-functions is obsolete, use -falign-functions");
1113 if (value > MAX_CODE_ALIGN)
1114 error_at (loc, "-malign-functions=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1115 value, MAX_CODE_ALIGN);
1116 else
1117 opts->x_align_functions = 1 << value;
1118 return true;
1119
1120 case OPT_mbranch_cost_:
1121 if (value > 5)
1122 {
1123 error_at (loc, "-mbranch-cost=%d is not between 0 and 5", value);
1124 opts->x_ix86_branch_cost = 5;
1125 }
1126 return true;
1127
1128 default:
1129 return true;
1130 }
1131}

1134 {
1135 /* Enable redundant extension instructions removal at -O2 and higher. */
1136 { OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS, OPT_free, NULL, 1 },
1137 /* Enable function splitting at -O2 and higher. */
1138 { OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS, OPT_freorder_blocks_and_partition, NULL, 1 },
1139 /* The STC algorithm produces the smallest code at -Os, for x86. */
1140 { OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS, OPT_freorder_blocks_algorithm_, NULL,
1141 REORDER_BLOCKS_ALGORITHM_STC },
1142 /* Turn off -fschedule-insns by default. It tends to make the
1143 problem with not enough registers even worse. */
1144 { OPT_LEVELS_ALL, OPT_fschedule_insns, NULL, 0 },

1147 SUBTARGET_OPTIMIZATION_OPTIONS,
1148#endif
1149 { OPT_LEVELS_NONE, 0, NULL, 0 }
1150 };

1152/* Implement TARGET_OPTION_INIT_STRUCT. */
1153
1154static void
1155ix86_option_init_struct (struct gcc_options *opts)
1156{
1157 if (TARGET_MACHO)
1158 /* The Darwin libraries never set errno, so we might as well
1159 avoid calling them when that's the only reason we would. */
1160 opts->x_flag_errno_math = 0;
1161
1162 opts->x_flag_pcc_struct_return = 2;
1163 opts->x_flag_asynchronous_unwind_tables = 2;
1164}

1166/* On the x86 -fsplit-stack and -fstack-protector both use the same
1167 field in the TCB, so they can not be used together. */
1168
1169static bool
1170ix86_supports_split_stack (bool report ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
1171 struct gcc_options *opts ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
1172{
1173 bool ret = true;
1174
1175#ifndef TARGET_THREAD_SPLIT_STACK_OFFSET
1176 if (report)
1177 error ("%<-fsplit-stack%> currently only supported on GNU/Linux");
1178 ret = false;
1179#else
1180 if (!HAVE_GAS_CFI_PERSONALITY_DIRECTIVE)
1181 {
1182 if (report)
1183 error ("%<-fsplit-stack%> requires "
1184 "assembler support for CFI directives");
1185 ret = false;
1186 }
1187#endif
1188
1189 return ret;
1190}

1192/* Implement TARGET_EXCEPT_UNWIND_INFO. */
1193
1194static enum unwind_info_type
1195i386_except_unwind_info (struct gcc_options *opts)
1196{
1197 /* Honor the --enable-sjlj-exceptions configure switch. */
1198#ifdef CONFIG_SJLJ_EXCEPTIONS
1199 if (CONFIG_SJLJ_EXCEPTIONS)
1200 return UI_SJLJ;
1201#endif
1202
1203 /* On windows 64, prefer SEH exceptions over anything else. */
1204 if (TARGET_64BIT && DEFAULT_ABI == MS_ABI && opts->x_flag_unwind_tables)
1205 return UI_SEH;
1206
1207 if (DWARF2_UNWIND_INFO)
1208 return UI_DWARF2;
1209
1210 return UI_SJLJ;
1211}
